---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms and Conditions — TT Motorcycle School"
  description="Terms and conditions for training at TT Motorcycle School. Please read before booking."
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="section__eyebrow">Legal</span>
      <h1 class="page-hero__title">Terms &amp; Conditions</h1>
      <p class="page-hero__sub">
        Please read the following terms carefully before booking or attending training
        with TT Motorcycle School.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="prose tc-prose">
        <p><em>Last updated: [Date]</em></p>

        <h2>1. Bookings</h2>
        <p>
          All bookings must be made in advance through our online booking system or by contacting
          us directly. A booking is confirmed only once payment has been received in full (or a
          deposit where applicable). TT Motorcycle School reserves the right to refuse or cancel
          bookings at its sole discretion.
        </p>

        <h2>2. Payment</h2>
        <p>
          Payment is required in full at the time of booking unless otherwise agreed. Accepted
          payment methods are listed at checkout. All prices are as stated on our
          <a href="/prices/">Prices page</a> at the time of booking.
        </p>

        <h2>3. Cancellation & Rescheduling</h2>
        <p>
          If you need to cancel or reschedule your booking, please contact us as soon as possible.
          The following policy applies:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>More than 7 days' notice:</strong> Full refund or free rescheduling</li>
          <li><strong>2–7 days' notice:</strong> 50% refund or rescheduling subject to availability</li>
          <li><strong>Less than 48 hours' notice or no-show:</strong> No refund</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          TT Motorcycle School reserves the right to cancel or reschedule sessions due to
          adverse weather, instructor illness, or other circumstances beyond our control.
          In such cases, a full refund or alternative date will be offered.
        </p>

        <h2>4. Eligibility</h2>
        <p>
          You must hold a valid UK provisional or full driving licence appropriate to the category
          of training booked. You are responsible for ensuring you meet all legal requirements
          to participate in training. TT Motorcycle School accepts no liability for bookings
          made by ineligible persons.
        </p>
        <p>
          You must be able to pass a basic eyesight test (reading a number plate at 20 metres
          in good daylight). You must not be under the influence of alcohol or drugs.
        </p>

        <h2>5. Clothing & Safety Equipment</h2>
        <p>
          You must attend training wearing appropriate clothing as described on our
          <a href="/what-to-wear/">What to Wear</a> page. Training cannot begin if you arrive in
          unsuitable clothing. No refund will be issued if training cannot proceed due to
          inadequate protective clothing.
        </p>

        <h2>6. Health & Medical</h2>
        <p>
          You must inform TT Motorcycle School of any medical condition, disability, or
          prescribed medication that may affect your ability to ride safely. We reserve the
          right to refuse or halt training if we believe it is unsafe to continue.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Liability</h2>
        <p>
          TT Motorcycle School takes every reasonable precaution to ensure the safety of
          students during training. However, motorcycle training involves inherent risks.
          TT Motorcycle School, its instructors, and agents accept no liability for personal
          injury, loss, or damage arising from training, except where caused by our own
          negligence.
        </p>
        <p>
          Training motorcycles are covered by the school's own insurance. Any damage caused
          to a training motorcycle through wilful misconduct or gross negligence may be
          charged to the student.
        </p>

        <h2>8. Code of Conduct</h2>
        <p>
          We expect all students to behave respectfully towards our instructors and fellow
          students. TT Motorcycle School reserves the right to terminate training without
          refund in cases of abusive, threatening, or dangerous behaviour.
        </p>

        <h2>9. Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          Your personal data is processed in accordance with UK GDPR. We collect only the
          information needed to deliver training and manage your booking. We do not sell or
          share your data with third parties without your consent, except where required by law.
        </p>

        <h2>10. Changes to These Terms</h2>
        <p>
          TT Motorcycle School reserves the right to update these terms at any time. The
          version published on this page at the time of your booking will apply.
        </p>

        <h2>11. Governing Law</h2>
        <p>
          These terms are governed by the laws of England and Wales. Any disputes shall be
          subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of England and Wales.
        </p>

        <hr />
        <p>
          For any questions regarding these terms, please <a href="/contact/">contact us</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .tc-prose {
    max-width: 760px;
  }

  .prose hr {
    border: none;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    margin-block: var(--space-8);
  }

  .prose a {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
</style>
